title: For Sale/Trade:  1986-1990 Glock G17 Mag
postcontent: I have one of the early samples of Glock G17 magazines.  It is a generation 3 magazine; there have been 9 generations of Glock mags, not the same as handgun model generations.Shown in the photos below, the right side with the mag catch slot shows four dimples.  The back of the magazine has the standard hole counter, plus two dimples between shot holes 15 & 17 and 14 & 16.  The back top sports the rounded slot of the slide to pick up the round and DOES NOT INDICATE 9MM.  The left side of the mag shows smaller dimples corresponding to the right.I come to the age estimation as the Glock handgun was first imported into the US in 1986.  Glock started multiple calibers in 1990.  Before that, there was no reason to show the 9MM on the mag.  I'm guessing, there is a Glock collector out there that would like to own piece of Glock history.  Asking price in $50, shipping to lower 48 extra.SILVER DISCOUNT  $5 in US 90% silver coin of dimes, quarters, halves or dollars minted 1964 or before.  Priority Mail shipping included with SILVER DISCOUNT purchase.Trade: I would trade for two (2) Glock OEM 33 rd 9MM magazines, no aftermarkets.OBO
